Gift to Kim Jong Il from C.C., Vietnam General Confederation of Labor 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, October 25 (KCNA) -- General Secretary Kim Jong Il was presented with a gift by the Central Committee of the Vietnam General Confederation of Labor. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It was handed to Kim Jung Rin, secretary of the Central Committee of the Workers' Party of Korea, by Senior Vice-President of its Central Committee Nguyen Hoa Binh on a visit to the DPRK Thursday.

Floral Tribute Paid to Fallen Fighters of CPV  
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, October 25 (KCNA) -- Wreaths were laid before the Friendship Tower in Pyongyang Thursday on the occasion of the 57th anniversary of the entry of the Chinese People's Volunteers (CPV) into the Korean front. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Present at the wreath-laying ceremony were Choe Yong Rim, secretary general of the Presidium of the DPRK Supreme People's Assembly, Pak Jae Gyong, vice-minister of the People's Armed Forces, Kim Yong Il, vice-minister of Foreign Affairs, and others. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Placed before the tower was a wreath in the joint name of the Central Committee of the Workers' Party of Korea and the SPA Presidium and the Cabinet of the DPRK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Also placed before the tower were wreaths in the name of the Ministry of the People's Armed Forces, the Foreign Ministry, the Ministry of People's Security, the Ministry of Foreign Trade and the Ministry of Culture, a wreath in the joint name of the Korean Committee for Cultural Relations with Foreign Countries and the Central Committee of the DPRK-China Friendship Association and a wreath in the joint name of the Pyongyang City Committee of the WPK and the Pyongyang City People's Committee. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The participants observed a moment's silence in memory of the fallen fighters of the CPV. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A wreath in the joint name of the Pyongyang City Committee of the WPK and the Pyongyang City People's Committee, a wreath in the joint name of the Hyongjesan District, Pyongyang City, Committee of the WPK and the Hyongjesan District People's Committee and a wreath in the name of a unit of the Korean People's Army were laid before the cemetery of fallen fighters of the CPV in Hyongjesan District on Thursday. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Chinese embassy here and the Central Committee of the Association of Chinese Residents in Korea placed wreaths before the tower and the cemetery on the same day.

Greetings to Kazakh President 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, October 25 (KCNA) -- Kim Yong Nam, president of the Presidium of the DPRK Supreme People's Assembly, sent a message of greetings to Nursultan Nazarbayev, President of Kazakhstan, Thursday on the occasion of its national day. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 In the message, Kim wholeheartedly wished the Kazakh president greater success in his responsible work and his people prosperity and welfare.

Anniversary of CPV's Entry into Korean Front Marked
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, October 25 (KCNA) -- Today marks the 57th anniversary of the entry of the Chinese People's Volunteers into the Korean front. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 On this occasion the men and officers of the Korean People's Army and the people of the DPRK extend friendly greetings to the men and officers of the Chinese People's Liberation Army and the people of China and pay high tribute to all the fighters of the CPV who fell while bravely fighting on the Korean front, Rodong Sinmun today says in a signed article. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It goes on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Korean people are now looking back with deep emotion upon the spirit of heroic struggle displayed by the brave fighters of the CPV, their comradeship and shining feats performed by them. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The traditional DPRK-China friendship has steadily grown stronger despite global ordeals and upheaval. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The history of the friendship is given steady continuity in the new century. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is the intention of the top leaders of the two countries and wishes of their peoples to boost the friendship generation after generation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The bilateral friendly and cooperative relations are favorably developing as the days go by under the deep care of the top leaders of the two countries and this pleases the two peoples. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Chinese people are working hard to build a harmoniously developed socialist society based on the scientific outlook on development under the guidance of the Communist Party of China with Hu Jintao as its general secretary. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Korean people sincerely wish the Chinese people good results in their efforts to realize socialist modernization with Chinese characteristics and reunify the whole country. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Minju Joson in a signed article devoted to this day notes that the fighters of the CPV displayed matchless courage, self-sacrificing spirit and heroism in the great Fatherland Liberation War of the Korean people after participating in it under the banner of "Resisting America and aiding Korea, safeguarding the home and defending the motherland."

Japanese Militarists' Moves for Overseas Aggression under Fire
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, October 25 (KCNA) -- The Japanese militarist forces are going more reckless in their bid to realize their ambition for overseas aggression by taking advantage of the prevailing situation where the balance of forces have changed on the international arena since the end of the Cold War and the U.S. has become evermore undisguised in its "war on terrorism." &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Rodong Sinmun Thursday observes this in a signed article. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Japanese militarists are availing themselves of all opportunities and conditions to realize the old dream of the "Greater East Asia Co-Prosperity Sphere" which they failed to do in the past, the article says, and goes on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Liberal Democratic Party and the ruling forces are contemplating instituting a new law to replace a "law on special measures against terrorism" in a bid to legally dispatch the "Self-Defence Forces" (SDF) to areas necessitated by them overseas for operation without getting the Diet approval. The proposed new law differs from the present law in that it restricts the SDF's search and support to disaster-stricken people, confines its activities to oil and water supply to warships of other countries and limits the period of the proposed law to one year. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Democratic Party, too, is opposed to extension of the "law on special measures against terrorism" but stands for the SDF's overseas military operations its own way. This party seeks to expand overseas military operations by letting the SDF join the "international security forces" created according to a resolution of the UN Security Council in December 2001, not favoring the SDF's dispatch overseas in line with the above-said law. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Japanese reactionaries' loudmouthed "Japan's contribution to peace" is, in essence, a slogan for overseas aggression and for a war to conquer the world. They are working hard to let the SDF conduct overseas military operations for aggression unhindered under the pretext of "contribution to global peace." Lurking behind this call is their sinister intention to launch reinvasion. The materialization of this intention would put global peace and security at greater peril. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Japanese militarists' moves for reinvasion are inching close to a danger line.

All Koreans Called upon to Remain True to Idea of "By Our Nation Itself"
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, October 25 (KCNA) -- The movement for national reunification is greeting a new heyday under the banner of "By our nation itself", declares Rodong Sinmun Thursday in a signed article. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Korean nation will before long put an end to the long history of national division and greet the new morning of independent reunification in this land resplendent with the august name of President Kim Il Sung and proud of the dignity of the great brilliant commander of Songun, it notes, and goes on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 "By our nation itself" means warm national ties linking Mt. Paektu and Mt. Halla and a powerful driving force uniting the Koreans as one. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is associated with the history of noble patriotism cherished by the peerlessly great men. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The idea of "By our nation itself" is the result of the unshakable conviction and will of Kim Jong Il to carry out the last instructions of the President on reunification at any cost, means a reunification programme based on his noble patriotic idea and an ever-victorious signpost promising a brilliant victory of the cause of reunification. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 How to approach the idea of "By our nation itself" precisely means a touchstone distinguishing a patriot from a traitor. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 This idea helps usher in a new era of national reunification and prosperity by dint of the ties and history of a homogeneous nation. Today all the Koreans stake their destiny on this idea, enshrining the truth that they will win when united and suffer a defeat when dispersed. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 How ardently one loves the nation shows what strong patriotic will one has to free the nation from misfortune and sufferings. One's devoted service to the nation means how totally one is dedicated to the cause of reunification. If one swims with the trend of the June 15 era of reunification, one will become a patriot, but if one fails to do so, one will become a social outcast in the times.

Names of Places to Be Conveyed along with Songun Era
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, October 25 (KCNA) -- Many steep heights and posts, towns and villages, big and small, have become famous in the DPRK as the witness of the Songun revolutionary history of Kim Jong Il, the brilliant commander of Mt. Paektu. Among them are the Tapaksol Post (covered with branchy young pine trees), Chol Pass, Mt. Osong, Kanggye, Thaechon, Poman-ri and others. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
�@In the grim trial period when the destiny of the country was at stake, he overcame the severe difficulties with the People's Army as the pillar of the revolution, covering the long journey for Songun all along. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
�@He called on the soldiers on Cho Island in the teeth of rough sea and found precious time to wait for a soldier in the blizzards on Chol Pass. There had been created so many legend-like stories showing the closest ties between the Supreme Commander and the soldiers. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
�@The love for and trust in the people shown by him while visiting many units during the unprecedented "Arduous March" and the forced march constituted the motive force which enabled them to bridge over the grave trials and make a breakthrough for the building of a great, prosperous and powerful nation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
�@The Kanggye Spirit was created by his energetic field guidance to Jagang Province made in the coldest period of the winter. And the torch of Songgang and Ranam and the Thaechon spirit brought about miracles and innovations in the building of the great, prosperous and powerful socialist nation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
�@Taehongdan County located in northern highland of the country is associated with stories about the paternal love of Kim Jong Il who led the efforts to make an innovation in the potato farming and dropped in a house of discharged soldiers and named the child to be born. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
�@The army and people of Korea hardened their faith in a brighter future, following his long journey for Songun. They rearranged land of the country as large-sized standard fields and built tremendous edifices in different parts including the gravity-fed irrigation channels and large hydro-power stations. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
�@Such famous places associated with an iron-like faith and pluck of Kim Jong Il to bring President Kim Il Sung's plan for building a rich and powerful nation into practice and his warm love and devotion for the people will be long conveyed down through history.

National Scientific and Technological Presentation Held
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, October 25 (KCNA) -- A national scientific and technological presentation was held at the Grand People's Study House on Oct. 23 and 24 on the occasion of the foundation anniversary of the State Academy of Sciences. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It was attended by scientists and technicians of scientific institutions, educational institutions, factories and enterprises from across the country. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Presented at the panel discussions in the fields of basic and ultra-modern science and technology, applied science and technology, bio-agricultural science and technology, chemistry, light industry and medical science and technology were at least 140 papers on the successes selected from the panel scientific and technological presentations held in August. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The participants exchanged successes and experience gained in putting the ultra-modern scientific and technological fields and technological engineering in key fields on a high level and accelerating the modernization of the national economy.

Little Boy Plays Six Kinds of Musical Instruments
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, October 25 (KCNA) -- A prodigy pupil is becoming the topic of a talk among art experts in the Democratic People's Republic of Korea as he plays six kinds of musical instruments. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Kim Hyok Song attending Kum Song School is extraordinarily sensitive to sound and rhythm. He understands deeper than what he has been taught. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He is now seven years old. He was taught how to play piano in Changgwang Kindergarten in Pyongyang from April, Juche 94 (2005). By September this year since then, he has learned how to perform six kinds of musical instruments. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He plays piano, various kinds of electronic organs with keyboards and percussion instruments. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Art experts say in unison that it is hard to see such young boys as Hyok Song who performs well the various kinds of musical instruments and his part in any ensemble.
 Even foreigners and overseas Koreans who visited the DPRK marveled at his technique of skillfully playing musical instruments.

Anniversary of Solidarity for Implementing Joint Declaration Marked in S. Korea
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, October 25 (KCNA) -- The Solidarity for Implementing the South-North Joint Declaration reportedly held a meeting at the Chungang University in Seoul on Oct. 20 to mark its 7th founding anniversary. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Kwon O Chang, permanent co-representative of the organization, Im Jae Bok, permanent representative of the Kwangju-South Jolla Provincial Solidarity for Implementing the South-North Joint Declaration, and other speakers said at the meeting that the organization has registered remarkable successes in the movement for independence, democracy and reunification over the last seven years, stressing the need to further expand and strengthen the organization with the conviction of victory. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A special resolution read out at the meeting stated that the long march of the 70 million fellow countrymen toward the prosperous era of reunification and the era of peace free from the U.S. forces is forcefully approaching its terminal. The victory of the nation on this road is certain, it declared. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It noted that the U.S. and the pro-U.S. conservatives are running amuck in the efforts to place the Grand National Party in power, dreaming of return to the era of the Cold War and fascism against this trend. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It expressed the determination to create a socio-political climate for national reunification and the pullout of U.S. forces by waging a pan-national movement for the full implementation of the June 15 joint declaration and, through this, build a grand alliance front against the conservatives so as to check without fail the attempts of the GNP to grab power. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The participants of the meeting saw a video on the anti-U.S. and anti-GNP struggle.

WPK's Birthday Marked in Different Countries
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, October 25 (KCNA) -- Film shows took place in Russia, Iran and Guinea from Oct. 3 to 9 on the occasion of the 62nd anniversary of the Workers' Party of Korea. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The participants of the events watched Korean films "The Great Leader Comrade Kim Jong Il Provides On-site Guidance to Work in Different Fields", "For the Liberation of the Country", "The Great Leader Victoriously Steering the Building of a Great Prosperous Powerful Nation" and "We Will Follow You to the End of the Earth".&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Several figures gave impressions of the films. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The garrison commander of the General Bureau for the Protection of the Guinean Presidency noted that the great Songun policy is an original political mode which the world progressives should follow and the Korean people could have a sure guarantee for building a reunified powerful nation in the near future thanks to this effective political mode. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The directors of several companies of Russia said that the Korean people are sure to always emerge victorious thanks to the wise leadership of Kim Jong Il, wishing them greater success in their efforts to build a great prosperous powerful socialist nation and achieve the reunification of the country.

Birthday of DIU Marked in Britain
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, October 25 (KCNA) -- The British Association for the Study of Songun Policy posted a special write-up illustrated with a photo of President Kim Il Sung on its Internet homepage on the occasion of the 81st anniversary of the formation of the Down-with-Imperialism Union (DIU). &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The special write-up titled "The ever-victorious Workers' Party of Korea is a revolutionary party which inherited the traditions of the DIU" gave a detailed account of the fact that the DIU served as the roots of the Korean revolution as it was the first organization of the genuine revolutionaries of the new generation in the history of the Korean revolution. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Referring to the immediate task and ultimate goal of the DIU, the homepage stressed that the WPK would always emerge victorious under the wise guidance of Kim Jong Il as it inherited the traditions of the DIU.

Conmemoran dia de participacion de voluntarios chinos en frente coreano 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Pyongyang, 25 de octubre (ATCC) -- Hoy se cumplen los 57 anos desde cuando los voluntarios militares del pueblo chino participaron en el frente coreano contra los agresores yanquis. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
�@Con motivo de esa efemeride, los oficiales y soldados del Ejercito Popular y el pueblo de Corea envian el saludo amistoso a sus homologos chinos y expresan sublime homenaje a todos los martires del ejercito de voluntarios chinos quienes lucharon con valentia en el frente coreano. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
�@Asi comienza un articulo individual insertado en la edicion de este jueves del diario Rodong Sinmun y continua: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
�@El pueblo coreano recuerda con emocion el espiritu de la lucha heroica, la camaraderia y las brillantes proezas de los voluntarios militares del pueblo chino. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
�@La tradicional amistad Corea-China ha venido fortaleciendose y desarrollandose sin cesar aun en medio de pruebas y reveces mundiales. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
�@La historia de tal amistad continua tambien hoy del nuevo siglo. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
�@Estrecharla de generacion en generacion es la voluntad de los dirigentes de los dos paises y el deseo de los dos pueblos. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
�@Bajo la gran atencion de los Dirigente de ambos paises, las relaciones binacionales de amistad y cooperacion se desarrollan cada dia mas favorablemente, lo cual da alegria a los pueblos de los dos paises. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
�@Hoy en dia, el pueblo chino, bajo la direccion del Partido Comunista de China encabezado por el secretario general Hu Jintao, lucha dinamicamente por acelerar la construccion de una armoniosa sociedad socialista basada en la concepcion de desarrollo cientifico. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
�@El pueblo coreano desea de todo corazon al pueblo chino buenos resultados en la lucha por la modernizacion socialista al estilo chino y la reunificacion de todo el pais. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
�@A su vez, el periodico Minju Joson, en su articulo individual, senala que los voluntarios militares chinos, participantes en la Guerra de la Liberacion de la Patria del pueblo coreano bajo la bandera de "Resistamos la agresion de EE.UU., ayudemos a Corea, protejamos el hogar y defendamos la patria", manifestaron la audacia, el espiritu de sacrificio y el heroismo sin pares.
